body: Hi @Suburbreverberation, is there an error message in the terminal? And how many records does the dataset have? Does the export result option work?

Hi, thank you for your answer. There are 461 records. The problem occurred with all the three projects I did. The download results works well but not the export.



[doc1.docx](https://github.com/asreview/asreview/files/5392223/doc1.docx)
Can you share the version of the software (see left menu)? Can you copy the content of the terminal?
The content of the terminal is in the docx attached in the previous message. version ASReview LAB 0.13

@Suburbreverberation, sorry for the inconvenience. This is a bug in ASReview version 0.13. We are working on a fix, but it takes a little longer. The fix will be available before the end of this week.
No problem, thank you for your answer. Do I need to download ASReview again once the problem will be solved?

@Suburbreverberation once the problem is solved, you can upgrade ASReview by running

`pip install --upgrade asreview`
Thanks a lot for reporting this bug. You can upgrade right now.

Well done @J535D165 !!

And many thanks @Suburbreverberation for reporting this bug! Do let us know if you experience any more problems. And if not: enjoy working with ASReview!!
